Description: AIMS OS — boot splash, login theme, wallpapers and icons
 This metapackage carries the AIMS Senegal visual identity that
 transforms a default Debian + GNOME installation into AIMS OS:
 .
   * a Plymouth boot splash with the AIMS circular Africa logo
   * a GRUB bootloader theme matching the AIMS visual identity
   * default and lock-screen wallpapers
   * a GNOME shell theme accent colour aligned with AIMS terracotta
   * /etc/os-release / /etc/issue / /etc/motd identifying AIMS OS
   * the AIMS application icon for the GNOME launcher
 .
 None of the dconf or GNOME settings shipped here are LOCKED; users
 remain free to change wallpaper, theme, icons and everything else
 to taste. Removing this package leaves a vanilla GNOME desktop on
 top of the AIMS OS scientific stack.
